# TypeScript Library Rules

- Prefer explicit public types.
- Keep implementation details out of the public API.
- Avoid `any` unless there is a clear interoperability reason.
- Preserve tree-shakable library design.
- Keep the core package framework-agnostic.
- Run typecheck, lint, and tests after meaningful changes.
